      "text": "Theo drags himself up the hill road. His head pounds, but by evening the fever breaks -- it was exhaustion, not plague. He arrives at the villa as the **brigata** is finishing dinner.\n\nDioneo spots him first. 'Look! The city threw one back!'\n\nPampinea raises an eyebrow. 'You changed your mind.'\n\n'I learned something down there,' Theo says. 'About what happens when there are no stories. People lose their minds. They drink until they can't feel, or they pray until they can't think, or they just sit in doorways waiting. Stories are the only thing that still makes sense.'\n\nPampinea smiles. 'Then you've already understood the first lesson. Sit down. Tomorrow we begin.'",
