      "title": "The First Day: Your Turn",
      "text": "The morning is bright. They sit in the garden under a pergola heavy with jasmine. Pampinea declares the first day open: no set theme -- speak on any subject you please.\n\nThe tales begin. **Panfilo** tells of **Ser Ciappelletto**, a wicked man who makes such a convincing false confession on his deathbed that the friar actually canonizes him. The brigata laughs, but nervously -- the tale asks whether we can ever truly know another person.\n\nThen Neifile tells the tale of **Melchisedech and the Three Rings**: when Saladin asks a Jewish merchant which of the three great religions is the true one, Melchisedech answers with a parable about three identical rings -- no one can tell the original from the copies. It's the most elegant dodge Theo has ever heard.\n\nNow it's Theo's turn. Pampinea looks at him expectantly.\n\nHe doesn't know a medieval tale. But he knows stories.",
